    subtitle: 'The designer who brought genuine literary ambition to the point-and-click adventure — and why Gabriel Knight remains one of the most sophisticated narratives gaming has produced',
    category: 'profile',
    summary: 'Jane Jensen joined Sierra On-Line in 1989 and created Gabriel Knight, a mystery series that treated the adventure game format as a serious literary vehicle. Her career is the case for what the genre could have become if commercial forces had allowed it.',
